The paper deals with image analysis and computer vision techniques for retinal images. Specifically, it proposes a method for finding line co-occurrence statistics from the centerlines of blood vessels in retinal images and using it for automated grouping of interrupted vessels. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves statistical modeling and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with geometric reasoning and pattern recognition, which are relevant to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.GR).
